# Grammar & Formatting

## Capitalization
**Use sentence case for everything:** nav items, headings, buttons, checkboxes, menus, forms, tooltips, radio buttons, tables.

| Element | Good | Bad |
|---------|------|-----|
| Heading | Send event data to Axiom | Send Event Data to Axiom |
| Button | Sign up | Sign Up |
| After colon | You and Axiom: The perfect pair | You and Axiom: the perfect pair |

**Brands:** Avoid scare caps (✓ Ebay ✗ eBay). Exception: iPhone.

## Numbers & Units
- Space between number and unit: ✓ 215 GB ✗ 215GB
- No space for B/M/K abbreviations: ✓ 215B ✗ 215 B

## Gender
Use singular "they": *A user enters their login credentials.*

## Abbreviations
- Spell out on first use: *binary large object (blob)*
- Use "for example" not "e.g." — "etc." is acceptable

## Links

| Rule | Good | Bad |
|------|------|-----|
| Don't include articles/punctuation in link | see the [Google docs](url). | see [the Google docs.](url) |
| Code element description outside link | use the [`width`](url) property | use the [`width` property](url) |
| No "click here" | see [Google docs](url) | click [here](url) |
| Cross-reference format | For more information, see [Title](url). | — |

**Contrary to Google:** External links open in new tab.

## Lists
- Introduce with complete sentence ending in colon
- Use numbered lists for sequential procedures
- Use bulleted lists for non-sequential items
- **Contrary to Google:** No lettered lists

## Punctuation
- **Oxford comma:** ✓ before, during, and after ✗ before, during and after
- Comma after introductory phrase: *Based on this information, Axiom calculates...*
- Comma in conditionals when clause comes first

## Spelling
- American English (see [Merriam-Webster](https://www.merriam-webster.com/))
- Compound words: email, online, website, webpage, ebook
- setup/login (noun) vs set up/log in (verb)

## Vocabulary
- No "please"
- No first-person plural: ✓ "Axiom recommends" ✗ "We recommend"
- "data" is singular: *Your data is safe.*
- Use "for example" not "for instance"
- Use "and" not "&" (except proper names)
- Ellipsis (…) in menus for destroy actions requiring confirmation

